From tgl Tom Lane Subject Re Vatican library Reposted by request these images are great but they are also LARGE pixels is a typical size Be regards tom lane From Roger Squires Newsgroups Subject Vatican Library Exhibit at Library of Congress ONLINE Date Feb GMT X Original Newsgroups X Original Date Feb GMT Archive name auto Vatican Library Exhibit at Library of Congress ONLINE This is from another newsgroup looks quite rms ANNOUNCING a new ONLINE EXHIBIT from THE LIBRARY OF CONGRESS ROME REBORN THE VATICAN LIBRARY RENAISSANCE CULTURE an Exhibit at the Library of Congress Washington DC Available by anonymous FTP from pub ROME REBORN THE VATICAN LIBRARY AND RENAISSANCE CULTURE presents some of the Vatican Library's most precious manuscripts books and maps many of which played a key role in the humanist recovery of the classical heritage of Greece and The exhibition presents the untold story of the Vatican Library as the intellectual driving force behind the emergence of Rome as a political and scholarly superpower during the The exhibit will be on display in the Jefferson Building of the Library of Congress from January through April The online exhibit will be available by anonymous FTP The exhibit is divided into nine sections The Vatican Library Archaeology Humanism Mathematics Music Medicine Biology Nature Described A Wider World I How the Orient Came to Rome and A Wider World II How Rome Went to Each section consists of its own sub directory within the exhibit directory and contains the exhibit text for that section and separate JPEG image files for each This online exhibit includes not only objects from the Library of Congress exhibit but also the alternate objects brought from Rome to be used if there were a problem with one of the primary objects and items omitted later in the planning This exhibit will be of interest to Medieval and Renaissance scholars in particular but also to art historians historians of science or medicine early music scholars students of the humanist movement students of printing and the printed word theologians scholars of both Far and Near Eastern studies and to librarians and information Please get the README file for details on what files this exhibit If you have questions about how to use FTP speak to your local computer support If you have questions or comments about the CONTENT of the exhibit please write to while if you have any questions or comments on the SYSTEM please contact Ellis Ellis Special Projects Office Library of Congress Washington DC Internet